duck: The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction - The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction is an English language reference work on science fiction, first published in 1979.
In 2006, it merged with the Australian Stock Exchange to form the Australian Securities Exchange.
Shannon-Fano-Elias coding, a lossless data compression algorithm
SparkFun Electronics - SparkFun Electronics is an electronics retailer in Boulder, Colorado, United States.

Secure function evaluation - Secure two-party computation (2PC) is sub-problem of secure multi-party computation (MPC) that has received special attention by researchers because of its close relation to many cryptographic tasks.
Stacking-fault energy - The stacking-fault energy is a material property on a very small scale.
Scouts for Equality - Scouts for Equality is a American advocacy organization that advocates for an end to the Boys Scouts of America's requirement that scouts and scout leaders be heterosexual.
Scottish Financial Enterprise - Scottish Financial Enterprise is the industry trade group that represents and promotes the interests of Scotland's international financial services industry.
Spec-Files-Extra, a way to build common packages for OpenSolaris or OpenIndiana
Supplier-furnished equipment - Supplier-furnished equipment In aviation, when an aircraft is made and delivered it will come with all agreed SFE equipment.
Supercritical fluid extraction - Supercritical Fluid Extraction is the process of separating one component from another using supercritical fluids as the extracting solvent.
Sigma Phi Epsilon - Sigma Phi Epsilon, commonly nicknamed SigEp or SPE, is a social college fraternity for male college students in the United States.
